(fifthQuint)Ultrasound Targeting for the Lumpectomy Cavity.

 Study participants will have weekly ultrasounds performed of the lumpectomy cavity to determine shift and volume changed from the initial treatment-planning CT to the time of the radiation boost (approximately 4 weeks).

 These ultrasounds are done prior to their weekly doctor's appointment with Radiation Oncology.

 When it is time to perform the radiation boost (when the radiation is more targeted to the lumpectomy cavity), the ultrasound will be done daily with the participant in treatment position.

 The SonArray system used for the ultrasound-driven targeting for prostate cancer will be utilized.

 If the lumpectomy cavity is observed, the ultrasound suggested shifts will be noted and compared to the shifts needed for standard clinical set up.

 Once the subject has completed radiation therapy, the study participation is complete.

